1
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:45,565
<i>For more than a year, ominous rumors
had been privately circulating...</i>

2
00:00:45,638 --> 00:00:48,072
<i>among high-level Western leaders...</i>

3
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:52,008
<i>that the Soviet Union had been at work
on what was darkly hinted to be...</i>

4
00:00:52,078 --> 00:00:55,776
<i>the ultimate weapon:
A doomsday device.</i>

5
00:00:55,849 --> 00:00:59,751
<i>Intelligence sources traced the site
of the top-secret Russian project...</i>

6
00:00:59,821 --> 00:01:02,517
<i>to the perpetually
fog-shrouded wasteland...</i>

7
00:01:02,590 --> 00:01:05,991
<i>below the Arctic peaks
of the Zhokhov Islands.</i>

8
00:01:06,060 --> 00:01:11,397
<i>What they were building or why it was
located in a remote, desolate place...</i>

9
00:01:11,467 --> 00:01:13,731
<i>no one could say.</i>

10
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:45,508
General Ripper, sir.

11
00:03:45,576 --> 00:03:47,510
Group Captain Mandrake speaking.

12
00:03:47,578 --> 00:03:49,569
This is General Ripper speaking.

13
00:03:49,647 --> 00:03:51,843
<i>- Yes, sir.
- Do you recognize my voice?</i>

14
00:03:51,917 --> 00:03:54,317
I do, sir. Why do you ask?

15
00:03:54,386 --> 00:03:56,149
Why do you think?

16
00:03:56,221 --> 00:03:59,817
I don't know, sir. We spoke
just a few moments ago, didn't we?

17
00:03:59,892 --> 00:04:05,125
You don't think I'd ask unless it was
pretty damned important, do you?

18
00:04:05,198 --> 00:04:06,632
No, I don't.

19
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,895
<i>Let's see if we can stay on the ball.</i>

20
00:04:09,836 --> 00:04:12,430
Has the Wing confirmed holding
at their fail-safe points?

21
00:04:12,506 --> 00:04:15,340
Yes, sir. The confirmations
have just come in.

22
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:19,039
Very well.
Now, listen to me carefully.

23
00:04:19,113 --> 00:04:21,912
The base is being put on condition red.

24
00:04:21,984 --> 00:04:24,214
I want this flashed
to all sections immediately.

25
00:04:24,286 --> 00:04:27,619
Condition red. Jolly good.
Keeps the men on their toes.

26
00:04:27,691 --> 00:04:29,955
This is not an exercise.

27
00:04:31,027 --> 00:04:32,892
Not an exercise?

28
00:04:34,598 --> 00:04:39,229
I shouldn't tell you this, but you're
a good officer and have a right to know.

29
00:04:39,303 --> 00:04:41,237
It looks like we're in a shooting war.

30
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:47,201
<i>- Oh, hell. Are the Russians involved?
- That's all I've been told.</i>

31
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:52,047
It came in on the red phone. I'm gonna
follow orders and seal this base tight.

32
00:04:53,152 --> 00:04:56,680
Now, I want you to transmit Plan R...

33
00:04:56,757 --> 00:04:58,691
R for Robert, to the Wing.

34
00:04:58,759 --> 00:05:02,160
<i>- Plan R for Robert.
- Is it that bad, sir?</i>

35
00:05:02,229 --> 00:05:04,721
<i>- Looks like it's pretty hairy.
- Yes, sir.</i>

36
00:05:04,799 --> 00:05:06,824
Plan R for Robert.

37
00:05:06,901 --> 00:05:10,234
Last and possibly most important...

38
00:05:10,305 --> 00:05:14,538
I want all privately owned radios
to be immediately impounded.

39
00:05:14,610 --> 00:05:18,547
They might be used to issue
instructions to saboteurs.

40
00:05:18,615 --> 00:05:21,482
As I previously arranged, Air Police
will have lists of all owners.

41
00:05:21,551 --> 00:05:25,545
I want every one collected
without exception.

42
00:05:25,623 --> 00:05:27,921
After you've done that,
report back to me.

43
00:05:55,057 --> 00:05:57,719
<i>In order to guard against
surprise nuclear attack...</i>

44
00:05:57,793 --> 00:06:01,230
<i>America's Strategic Air Command
maintains...</i>

45
00:06:01,297 --> 00:06:05,427
<i>a large force of B-52 bombers
airborne 24 hours a day.</i>

46
00:06:05,501 --> 00:06:10,405
<i>Each B-52 can deliver
a nuclear bomb load of 50 megatons...</i>

47
00:06:10,474 --> 00:06:15,503
<i>equal to 16 times the total
explosive force of all the bombs...</i>

48
00:06:15,580 --> 00:06:20,142
<i>and shells used by all the armies
in World War II.</i>

49
00:06:20,218 --> 00:06:23,347
<i>Based in America,
the Airborne Alert Force...</i>

50
00:06:23,422 --> 00:06:26,220
<i>is deployed from the Persian Gulf
to the Arctic Ocean.</i>

51
00:06:26,292 --> 00:06:29,090
<i>But they have one geographical factor
in common.</i>

52
00:06:29,161 --> 00:06:33,121
<i>They are all two hours
from their targets inside Russia.</i>

53
00:07:53,157 --> 00:07:56,150
Major Kong, I know you'll think
this is crazy...

54
00:07:56,228 --> 00:07:59,891
but I just got a message from base
over the C.R.M. 114.

55
00:08:00,966 --> 00:08:04,926
It decodes as Wing attack Plan R.
R for Romeo.

56
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:12,308
Goldie, did you say
Wing attack Plan R?

57
00:08:12,379 --> 00:08:13,903
Yes, sir, I have.

58
00:08:17,719 --> 00:08:22,418
Goldie, how many times have
I told you guys that I don't want...

59
00:08:22,491 --> 00:08:24,426
<i>horsin'around on the airplane?</i>

60
00:08:24,494 --> 00:08:26,758
I'm not horsing around.
That's how it decodes.

61
00:08:26,829 --> 00:08:29,491
I've been to one world fair,
a picnic...

62
00:08:29,565 --> 00:08:33,434
<i>and a rodeo, and that's the stupidest
thing I heard over earphones.</i>

63
00:08:33,504 --> 00:08:35,404
You sure you got today's code?

64
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,932
Yes, sir.

65
00:08:38,008 --> 00:08:40,569
There's gotta be something wrong.

66
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:43,011
Wait a second, I'm coming back.

67
00:09:17,487 --> 00:09:21,150
Maybe you'd better get
a confirmation from base.

68
00:09:21,224 --> 00:09:22,658
Yes, sir.

69
00:09:43,784 --> 00:09:46,378
Major Kong, is it possible
this is some kind of loyalty test?

70
00:09:46,453 --> 00:09:50,116
You know, give the go code and then
recall to see who would actually go?

71
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:54,321
Ain't nobody ever got
the go code yet.

72
00:09:54,395 --> 00:09:56,795
Old Ripper wouldn't be giving us
Plan R...

73
00:09:56,864 --> 00:09:59,493
unless them Ruskies had already
clobbered Washington...

74
00:09:59,568 --> 00:10:01,866
and a lot of other towns
with a sneak attack.

75
00:10:01,937 --> 00:10:03,199
Yes, sir.

76
00:10:03,272 --> 00:10:05,764
Major Kong,
message from base confirmed.

77
00:10:10,614 --> 00:10:12,981
Well, boys, I reckon this is it.

78
00:10:14,051 --> 00:10:17,316
Nuclear combat toe-to-toe
with the Ruskies.

79
00:10:32,372 --> 00:10:37,242
Boys, I ain't much of a hand
at making speeches.

80
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:41,979
But I got a fair idea
that something doggone important...

81
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:44,041
is going on back there.

82
00:10:44,119 --> 00:10:47,988
I've got a fair idea of the kind
of personal emotions...

83
00:10:48,057 --> 00:10:51,515
<i>that some of you fellows
may be thinking.</i>

84
00:10:51,594 --> 00:10:54,324
<i>Heck, I reckon you wouldn't be
human beings...</i>

85
00:10:54,397 --> 00:10:58,994
<i>if you didn't have pretty strong
personal feelings about nuclear combat.</i>

86
00:10:59,069 --> 00:11:02,005
<i>I want you to remember one thing.</i>

87
00:11:02,073 --> 00:11:04,837
<i>The folks back home
are counting on you.</i>

88
00:11:04,909 --> 00:11:07,241
<i>And by golly,
we ain't about to let them down.</i>

89
00:11:08,579 --> 00:11:11,378
Tell you something else.

90
00:11:11,450 --> 00:11:16,445
If this thing turns out to be half
as important as I figure it might be...

91
00:11:16,523 --> 00:11:20,550
I'd say you're all in line
for some important promotions...

92
00:11:20,627 --> 00:11:24,428
and personal citations
when this thing's over with.

93
00:11:24,498 --> 00:11:27,262
That goes for every last one of you...

94
00:11:27,334 --> 00:11:31,169
regardless of your race,
color or your creed.

95
00:11:31,239 --> 00:11:34,800
Now let's get this thing on the hump.
We got some flying to do.

96
00:11:48,425 --> 00:11:50,655
Buck, should I get it?

97
00:11:50,728 --> 00:11:52,663
Yeah, you'll have to.

98
00:11:58,603 --> 00:12:00,367
Hello?

99
00:12:00,439 --> 00:12:05,035
Yes, General Turgidson is here,
but he can't come to the phone now.

100
00:12:05,111 --> 00:12:07,376
This is his secretary, Miss Scott.

101
00:12:08,515 --> 00:12:10,710
Freddie, how are you?

102
00:12:10,784 --> 00:12:13,048
Fine. And you?

103
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:17,785
Oh, we were just catching up
on some of the general's paperwork.

104
00:12:17,859 --> 00:12:22,490
He's tied up.
I'm afraid he can't come to the phone.

105
00:12:23,565 --> 00:12:24,998
Just a minute.

106
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:28,333
General Turgidson,
a Colonel Puntrich calling.

107
00:12:28,404 --> 00:12:30,338
Tell him to call back.

108
00:12:30,406 --> 00:12:35,105
Freddie, the general says
could you call back in a minute?

109
00:12:35,179 --> 00:12:37,113
He says it can't wait.

110
00:12:37,181 --> 00:12:40,514
For Pete's...
Find out what he wants.

111
00:12:40,584 --> 00:12:44,487
The general is in the powder room
right now.

112
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:46,820
Could you tell me what it's about?

113
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:52,357
Just a second. Apparently they monitored
a transmission eight minutes ago...

114
00:12:52,431 --> 00:12:54,922
from Burpelson Air Force Base.

115
00:12:56,770 --> 00:13:01,833
Right. It was directed to
the 843rd Bomb Wing on airborne alert.

116
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:07,069
It decoded as Wing attack Plan R.

117
00:13:07,148 --> 00:13:12,815
Well, tell him to call what's-his-name,
Base Commander Ripper.

118
00:13:12,888 --> 00:13:14,549
Do I have to think of everything?

119
00:13:14,623 --> 00:13:19,220
The general suggests you call General
Ripper, the 843rd base commander.

120
00:13:19,296 --> 00:13:22,697
Oh. All communications are dead!

121
00:13:22,766 --> 00:13:26,168
Bull! Tell him to do it himself.

122
00:13:26,237 --> 00:13:31,174
The general asks if you could
possibly try again yourself.

123
00:13:31,242 --> 00:13:35,907
I see. He says he's tried personally
several times, but everything is dead.

124
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:38,745
Even the normal phone lines
are shut down.

125
00:13:46,025 --> 00:13:48,859
Fred? Buck.
What's it look like?

126
00:13:50,464 --> 00:13:51,897
Yeah?

127
00:13:53,334 --> 00:13:56,327
Well, are you sure
it's Plan R?

128
00:13:57,572 --> 00:14:00,268
Huh. What's cooking
on the threat board?

129
00:14:00,342 --> 00:14:03,141
Nothing? Nothing at all?

130
00:14:05,314 --> 00:14:07,373
I don't like the look of this.

131
00:14:08,852 --> 00:14:11,480
Tell you what you better do,
old buddy.

132
00:14:11,555 --> 00:14:14,718
You better give Elmo and Charlie a blast
and bump everything up to condition red.

133
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:17,352
Stand by the blower.
I'll get back to you.

134
00:14:17,428 --> 00:14:19,623
- What's up?
- Nothing.

135
00:14:21,199 --> 00:14:24,499
- Where's my shorts?
- On the floor. Where are you going?

136
00:14:24,570 --> 00:14:26,333
No place.

137
00:14:26,405 --> 00:14:31,139
I thought I might mosey over to the
War Room to see what's doing over there.

138
00:14:31,211 --> 00:14:33,008
It's 3:00 in the morning.

139
00:14:33,079 --> 00:14:35,013
The air force never sleeps.

140
00:14:35,081 --> 00:14:39,018
Buck, honey, I'm not sleepy either.

141
00:14:41,689 --> 00:14:44,488
I know how it is, baby.

142
00:14:44,559 --> 00:14:46,584
Tell you what you do.

143
00:14:47,629 --> 00:14:51,589
You start your countdown
and old Bucky will be back...

144
00:14:51,668 --> 00:14:55,229
before you can say "Blastoff!"

145
00:14:56,506 --> 00:15:00,603
<i>Your Commie has no regard
for human life, not even his own.</i>

146
00:15:01,779 --> 00:15:05,613
<i>For this reason, men, I want
to impress upon you the need...</i>

147
00:15:05,683 --> 00:15:07,777
<i>for extreme watchfullness.</i>

148
00:15:07,852 --> 00:15:11,879
<i>The enemy may come individually
or he may come in strength.</i>

149
00:15:11,957 --> 00:15:14,552
He may even come in the uniform
of our own troops.

150
00:15:15,528 --> 00:15:18,122
<i>But however he comes,
we must stop him.</i>

151
00:15:18,197 --> 00:15:20,962
<i>We must not allow him
to gain entrance to this base.</i>

152
00:15:22,502 --> 00:15:26,438
<i>Now, I am going to give you
three simple rules.</i>

153
00:15:26,506 --> 00:15:31,001
<i>First: Trust no one,
whatever his uniform or rank...</i>

154
00:15:31,079 --> 00:15:33,570
<i>unless he is known to you personally.</i>

155
00:15:33,648 --> 00:15:36,516
<i>Secondly: Anyone or anything...</i>

156
00:15:36,585 --> 00:15:41,488
that approaches within 200 yards
of the perimeter is to be fired upon.

157
00:15:41,557 --> 00:15:47,190
Third: If in doubt, shoot first
and ask questions afterwards.

158
00:15:47,263 --> 00:15:50,631
<i>I would sooner accept a few casualties
through accident...</i>

159
00:15:50,701 --> 00:15:54,831
<i>than lose the entire base
and its personnel through carelessness.</i>

160
00:15:54,905 --> 00:15:59,036
<i>Any variation on these rules
must come from me personally.</i>

161
00:16:00,112 --> 00:16:02,945
<i>Now, men, in conclusion...</i>

162
00:16:03,015 --> 00:16:07,077
<i>I would like to say
that in the two years...</i>

163
00:16:07,153 --> 00:16:10,954
<i>that it has been my privilege
to be your commanding officer...</i>

164
00:16:11,025 --> 00:16:13,960
<i>I have always expected
the best from you...</i>

165
00:16:14,028 --> 00:16:17,931
<i>and you have never given me
anything less than that.</i>

166
00:16:17,999 --> 00:16:21,366
<i>Today the nation is counting on us.</i>

167
00:16:22,437 --> 00:16:25,271
<i>We are not going to let them down.</i>

168
00:16:25,341 --> 00:16:27,275
<i>Good luck to you all.</i>

169
00:16:57,477 --> 00:17:00,002
Here's the attack profile, sir.

170
00:17:27,778 --> 00:17:30,441
This is your attack profile.

171
00:17:30,515 --> 00:17:33,609
"To ensure that the enemy cannot monitor
voice transmission...

172
00:17:33,685 --> 00:17:35,846
or plant false transmission...

173
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:41,052
the C.R.M. 114 is to be switched
into all receiver circuits.

174
00:17:41,127 --> 00:17:44,586
The emergency base code prefix
is to be set...

175
00:17:44,664 --> 00:17:47,064
<i>on the dials of the C.R.M.</i>

176
00:17:47,134 --> 00:17:51,697
<i>This will block any transmission other
than those preceded by a code prefix. "</i>

177
00:17:53,274 --> 00:17:55,435
Stand by to set code prefix.

178
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:57,979
Roger. Ready to set code prefix.

179
00:17:58,046 --> 00:17:59,911
"Set code prefix."

180
00:18:09,459 --> 00:18:10,892
Code prefix set.

181
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,622
"Lock code prefix."

182
00:18:15,299 --> 00:18:16,732
Code prefix locked.

183
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:20,293
"Switch all receiver circuits
to C.R.M. Discriminators."

184
00:18:21,506 --> 00:18:24,737
Switched to C.R.M. Discriminators.

185
00:18:24,809 --> 00:18:26,675
<i>"Check auto destruct circuits."</i>

186
00:18:29,982 --> 00:18:31,916
Auto destruct circuits checked.

187
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:41,728
"Primary target:
The I.C.B.M. Complex at Laputa.

188
00:18:41,796 --> 00:18:46,028
Target reference:
Yankee, golf, tango...

189
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:48,160
3-6-0.

190
00:18:48,237 --> 00:18:50,171
Thirty megaton nuclear device...

191
00:18:50,239 --> 00:18:54,335
<i>fused for air burst at 10,000 feet.</i>

192
00:18:54,410 --> 00:18:58,905
<i>Twenty megaton nuclear device
will be used if first malfunctions.</i>

193
00:18:58,982 --> 00:19:01,644
<i>Otherwise, proceed to secondary target:</i>

194
00:19:01,718 --> 00:19:05,746
<i>Missile complex seven miles east
of Borchov.</i>

195
00:19:05,823 --> 00:19:09,783
<i>Target reference:
November, bravo, Xray...</i>

196
00:19:09,861 --> 00:19:12,329
1-0-8.

197
00:19:12,397 --> 00:19:17,700
Fused air burst at 10..."
Check..."12,000 feet."

198
00:19:29,016 --> 00:19:32,919
Excuse me, sir. Something rather
interesting has just cropped up.

199
00:19:32,988 --> 00:19:35,821
Listen to that. Music.
Civilian broadcasting.

200
00:19:37,425 --> 00:19:41,692
I think the Pentagon has given us
an exercise to check our readiness.

201
00:19:41,764 --> 00:19:43,755
I think it's taking things too far.

202
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:46,860
Our fellows will be inside Russian
radar cover in about 20 minutes.

203
00:19:46,937 --> 00:19:50,168
Listen. Chock full of stations
all churning it out.

204
00:19:51,942 --> 00:19:53,706
- Mandrake?
- Yes, sir?

205
00:19:53,778 --> 00:19:57,214
I issued instructions for all radios
to be impounded.

206
00:19:57,282 --> 00:20:01,583
You did, and I was in the process of
impounding this when I switched it on.

207
00:20:01,654 --> 00:20:05,146
I thought our fellows hitting Russian
radar, dropping all their stuff...

208
00:20:05,224 --> 00:20:09,685
I'd better tell you because if they do,
it'll cause a stink.

209
00:20:09,763 --> 00:20:13,824
Group Captain,
the officer exchange program...

210
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:17,530
does not give you any special
prerogatives to question my orders.

211
00:20:17,605 --> 00:20:21,838
I realize that, sir, but I thought
you'd be pleased to hear the news.

212
00:20:21,910 --> 00:20:24,674
After all, let's face it.

213
00:20:24,746 --> 00:20:28,740
We don't want to start a nuclear war
unless we have to, do we?

214
00:20:29,719 --> 00:20:33,382
Please sit down.
And turn that thing off.

215
00:20:33,456 --> 00:20:34,582
Yes, sir.

216
00:20:34,657 --> 00:20:39,561
What about the planes? Surely we must
issue the recall code immediately.

217
00:20:39,630 --> 00:20:42,497
The planes are not going
to be recalled.

218
00:20:42,566 --> 00:20:45,434
My attack orders have been issued,
and the orders stand.

219
00:20:47,472 --> 00:20:51,637
If you'll excuse me for saying so,
that would be to my way of thinking...

220
00:20:51,711 --> 00:20:53,872
rather an odd way of looking at it

221
00:20:53,946 --> 00:20:56,346
If a Russian attack was in progress...

222
00:20:56,415 --> 00:21:00,352
we would certainly not be hearing
civilian broadcasting.

223
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:03,287
- Are you certain?
- I'm absolutely positive.

224
00:21:03,357 --> 00:21:06,088
What if it is true?

225
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:09,186
I'm afraid I'm still not with you, sir,
because I mean...

226
00:21:10,765 --> 00:21:13,132
if a Russian attack
was not in progress...

227
00:21:13,202 --> 00:21:17,571
then your use of Plan R... In fact,
your orders to the entire Wing...

228
00:21:25,048 --> 00:21:30,316
I would say, sir, that there was
something dreadfully wrong somewhere

229
00:21:31,389 --> 00:21:33,756
Why don't you take it easy,
